The paper discusses a framework for similarity search in large datasets, specifically in the domains of high-throughput drug screening, metagenomics, and protein structure search. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of entropy and fractal dimension to characterize datasets suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the mention of accelerated versions of standard tools suggests a possible connection to algorithms and complexity (cs.CC).
